---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Starting With Q — QUIZZIFY, QUARTZ, QUIRKY & QUINTET" description="Master Q-starting Scrabble words. QUIZZIFY (40pts), QUARTZ (24pts), QUIRKY (22pts), QUINTET (16pts). Q strategy with and without U for maximum scoring." keywords="scrabble words starting with q, quartz scrabble points, quirky scrabble, quintet scrabble word, q words scrabble, quizzify scrabble, words beginning with q">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Starting With Q — QUIZZIFY, QUARTZ, QUIRKY & QUINTET","description":"Master Q-starting Scrabble words. QUIZZIFY (40pts), QUARTZ (24pts), QUIRKY (22pts), QUINTET (16pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-starting-with-q"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What Q-starting words score highest in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUIZZIFY scores 40 points (Q=10, U=1, I=1, Z=10, Z=10, I=1, F=4, Y=4). QUARTZ scores 24 points, QUIRKY scores 22 points, and QUINTET scores 16 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUARTZ a good Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUARTZ is excellent — scoring 24 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10) in just 6 letters. It deploys both Q and Z, the two highest-value tiles, in one play. A DWS placement scores 48 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What Q words work without U in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key Q-without-U words include QI (11pts), QOPH (18pts), QADI (14pts), QANAT (14pts), QINTAR (15pts), and QWERTY (21pts). These let you play Q without needing U in your rack."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Letter Guides</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Starting With Q — QUIZZIFY, QUARTZ, QUIRKY & QUINTET</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Q is worth 10 points — the joint-highest tile value in Scrabble. But it's also the most feared tile because most Q words require U. Master Q-starting words and you'll turn that feared tile into a scoring machine. QUIZZIFY alone delivers 40 points without even hitting a premium square.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUIZZIFY</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">40 points — Q(10) + U(1) + I(1) + Z(10) + Z(10) + I(1) + F(4) + Y(4)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An 8-letter bingo candidate scoring 90 points with the bonus. Requires Q, both Z tiles, plus common letters — legendary when achievable.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Q-Starting Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 QUIZZIFY — 40 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q + both Z tiles + F + Y. The ultimate Q-word. Bingo = 90 total.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 QUARTZ — 24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10)+U(1)+A(1)+R(1)+T(1)+Z(10). Deploys Q and Z together. Classic.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤪 QUIRKY — 22 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10)+U(1)+I(1)+R(1)+K(5)+Y(4). K and Y add extra punch after Q.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎶 QUINTET — 16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10)+U(1)+I(1)+N(1)+T(1)+E(1)+T(1). All common tiles around Q.</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Q Without U — Emergency Plays</h2>
      <p>When you draw Q without U, these words save you from being stuck with a -10 penalty at game end.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QOPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QADI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QANAT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QWERTY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">21 pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Q-Word Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZ on a DWS:</span> At 24 base points, a Double Word Score gives you 48 points. Uses common tiles (U, A, R, T) alongside Q and Z — achievable with the right board position.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QI is your insurance policy:</span> QI (11pts) is the most important Q-word to know. It's 2 letters, needs no U, and scores 11 points minimum. On a TLS, the Q alone contributes 30 points. Always your fallback.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold Q with good company:</span> If you have Q + U + Z or Q + U + K + Y, you're looking at 22-40 point plays. Hold for 1-2 turns. If nothing materializes, dump Q via QI before it costs you the game.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Q Dilemma</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Q is the <span class="text-white font-medium">highest risk-reward tile</span> in Scrabble. It scores 10 points when played but costs you 10 when stuck at game end. Know enough Q-words (with AND without U) to always deploy it within 2 turns of drawing it.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble — Complete Scoring Guide</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/q-words-without-u/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Q Words Without U — Essential Scrabble List</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-starting-with-j/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Starting With J — JAZZY, JUKEBOX & More</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl"><div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap"><p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a></div></div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
